reviews.review_text: Big show woooooooohooooooo! A soundboard finally exists of my second best show I saw live(4/5/91 wins, hands down). And what a gorgeous sounding soundboard it is. Everything is mixed nicely right from the start, with plenty of crowd noise notch the x factor up a bit. A great show, with a peppy first set featuring a wonderful stand alone Franklin's Tower, and a BIG second set that just keeps on moving down the rails, culminating in a rockstar Throwin'/NFA that is the sort of thing we kept showing up for. The encore, only the 10th "Box" encore at that time, usually meant a stamp of approval from Phil, or so I've heard. It's superior to the one on Fallout From the Phil Zone, at least IMHO, done just perfectly as a lullaby to send us on our way. 5 stars, two thumbs up, and a parade for this show, just because of the performance, plus sound quality.

Thank you Charlie Miller!! This board is better than my wildest dreams for this show. Great second set. Ship, Playing>Foolish, sick drumz, and one of the fav. NFA's that I saw. This was the kick-off of a new lighting (the diamond??!! Those guys had the best seats!! XD) rig, and the band was putting it through it's paces at the Omni for sure!!

great show great recording of a great show. this was my 3rd Dead show, and my best up to that point. Afterward, was partying in a lot and got nabbed by the scariest 2 cops I,ve ever seen (red dog squad). They told me they were gonna beat the shit out me, but I was rescued by their supervisor. WHEW!
3-28-89 Another fine show from '89. Great sounding remaster ny Charlie as well.
3-28-1988 pardon my ignorance ... how can i download this version of the show?
Setlist What a great setlist! Especially a rocking, kick-ass first set. Love the LTGTR>Franklin's. Oh, and the sound quality is great, per usual for Charlie Miller and the great year that was 1989.
The song that woman sung was look out stagger lee!
PLAYIN! What a monster. Takes you on a sweet ride to heaven, hell and the outer reaches of the universe. The energy in foolish is way up there - fierce! Strong show
My First Show! Glad to finally get the SBD version. Aside from the guy constantly whistling during Drums/Space, this is a great recording!

Spring Tour Head Great Show Grate recording.  No Video available.
Just about every song is a good to excellent version of that song.  My bus, The Canibus parked at the Omni between these shows.  I slept in the bus on the lot on the first night.  Those of us who got to see The Lot scene before its implosion, know just how weird it could get in the wee hours.
GDT sent me Taper tickets so I heard every note so well.  The feeling inside that night was a Spring Tour vibe for sure. Fresh. Optimistic.
The Playing is both subtle and inspired.
The blonde Lebanese didn't hurt.

MY FIRST SHOW!!  My first show,  and what a doozy.
All i knew at the time was that I had arrived  - I had found my heart....
Years later,  knowing the material like I didn't then - and with a vast accumulated  frame of reference -  i get to listen with a smile from ear to ear because I KNOW what  an AMAZING show this was!!!
(Lucky me!!)

💜🌞🕉🎶
XOXO !!!

How Grate Thou Are  Of all the shows I attended, this one stands out. The flow of music this night was as good as it gets. Loved the people I was with and even tho we haven't talked in years, they are as special as the music. Miss them both equally.
